import pandas as pd

def process_data(filename):
    # Read the CSV file, skipping the first 4 rows
    df = pd.read_csv(filename, skiprows=4)

    # Drop unnecessary columns and rename for clarity
    df = df.drop(columns=['Country Code', 'Indicator Code', 'Unnamed: 67']).rename(columns={'Country Name': 'Country', 'Indicator Name': 'Indicator'})

    # Select a subset of countries
    target_countries = ['Australia', 'Brazil', 'Canada', 'Mexico', 'Russia', 'South Africa', 'South Korea', 'Turkey', 'United Arab Emirates']
    df = df.loc[df['Country'].isin(target_countries)]

    # Select specific indicators
    target_indicators = ['CO2 emissions (kt)',
                  'Agricultural land (sq. km)',
                  'Forest area (sq. km)',
                  'Population growth (annual %)','GDP (current US$)', 'Arable land (% of land area)', 'Renewable energy consumption (% of total final energy consumption)', 'Life expectancy at birth, total (years)']
    selected_df = df.loc[df['Indicator'].isin(target_indicators)]

    # Identify columns with numeric data and fill missing values
    numeric_columns = selected_df.select_dtypes(include=['number']).columns
    selected_df[numeric_columns] = selected_df[numeric_columns].apply(lambda row: row.fillna(row.mean()), axis=1)

    # Reset index for the selected DataFrame
    selected_df.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)

    # Melt DataFrame to convert years into rows
    melted_df = selected_df.melt(id_vars=['Country', 'Indicator'], var_name='Year', value_name='Value')

    # Pivot the melted DataFrame to have countries as columns
    pivoted_df = melted_df.pivot_table(index=['Year', 'Indicator'], columns='Country', values='Value').reset_index()

    # Remove the name of the index in the pivoted DataFrame
    processed_data_by_years = pivoted_df.rename_axis(None, axis=1)

    # Return two DataFrames: processed data by years and the selected data
    return processed_data_by_years, selected_df

# Define specific indicators of interest
selected_indicators = ['Arable land (% of land area)', 'GDP (current US$)']

# Filter the processed data by years DataFrame based on selected indicators
df_selected = df1[df1['Indicator'].isin(selected_indicators)]

# Calculate correlation matrix grouped by indicators
correlation_matrix = df_selected.groupby('Indicator').corr()

# Set up the visualization
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', fmt=".2f")

# Customize the plot
plt.title('Correlation Matrix of Selected Indicators')
plt.xlabel('Country')
plt.ylabel('Year-Indicator Pairs')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.yticks(rotation=0)
plt.tight_layout()

# Display the heatmap
plt.show()
